5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT APPROPRIATING MONEY FOR MAJOR REPAIR AND CAPITAL
6 DEVELOPMENT PROJECTS FOR THE BIENNIUM ENDING JUNE 30, 2027; PROVIDING FOR OTHER
7 MATTERS RELATING TO THE APPROPRIATIONS; PROVIDING FOR A TRANSFER OF FUNDS FROM THE
8 GENERAL FUND TO THE CAPITAL DEVELOPMENTS LONG-RANGE BUILDING PROGRAM ACCOUNT
9 AND A TRANSFER OF FUNDS FROM THE GENERAL FUND TO A STATE SPECIAL REVENUE FUND;
10 PROVIDING FOR A MODIFICATION TO THE LONG-RANGE BUILDING PROGRAM; INCREASING CERTAIN
11 VALUE THRESHOLDS FROM $150,000 TO $300,000; ESTABLISHING REPORTING REQUIREMENTS;
12 ALLOWING A COMBINATION OF PREVIOUSLY APPROVED APPROPRIATIONS FOR THE CLAPP
13 BUILDING; AMENDING SECTIONS 17-7-201, 17-7-202, 17-7-210, AND 17-7-223, MCA; AMENDING
14 SECTION 1, CHAPTER 468, LAWS OF 2021, SECTION 9(1), CHAPTER 739, LAWS OF 2023, SECTION
15 14(1), CHAPTER 762, LAWS OF 2023, AND SECTION 3, CHAPTER 763, LAWS OF 2023; AND PROVIDING
16 AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
17
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
19
20 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Definitions. For the purposes of [sections 1 through 10], unless
21 otherwise stated, the following definitions apply:
22 (1) "Authority only" means approval provided by the legislature to expend money that does not
23 require an appropriation, including grants, donations, auxiliary funds, proprietary funds, nonstate funds, and
24 university funds.
25 (2) "Capital development" has the same meaning as provided in 17-7-201(2).
26 (3) "Capital project" means the planning, design, renovation, construction, alteration, replacement,
27 furnishing, repair, improvement, site, utility, or land acquisition project provided for in [sections 1 through 10].
